  <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary05.jpg"/>
            <head><date>Saturday 14.</date></head>
            <p>We were out early at <time>nine o'clock</time> for the Division Review. We were reviewed by Gen
               Foster, Burnside no having arrived. The day was splendid, &amp; there were eleven
               Regts of infantry,<orgName> 21st</orgName>, <orgName>22</orgName>,<orgName>23</orgName>, <orgName>24</orgName>, <orgName>27 Mass </orgName><orgName>57th N.Y.</orgName> <orgName>61st</orgName> &amp; <orgName>11th Penn</orgName>  8th &amp; 
                     11th <orgName>Connecticut 33</orgName> <placeName>NY </placeName><persName>D'Epineuil</persName> [?] &amp; the Ira Harris cavalry.</p>
            
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary06.jpg"/>
            <fw><placeName key="Camp Union" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnp0l11">Camp Union</placeName>, <placeName key="Annapolis, MD" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002">Near Annapolis Md</placeName> </fw></div><div type="entry"><fw><date>December 14 Saturday continued</date></fw>
            <p>We got through by <time>two o'clock</time>. The performance of our <orgName>Regiment</orgName> was admirable.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
  </text>
